The 1970 Herald Saloon the boys are here to rescue is the property of Josephine. She had always dreamed of owning and driving a classic car , however about the same time she took on her rusting Herald her daughter became gravely ill. After a three year fight Josephines daughter passed away. Josephines desire to put her beloved Herald back on the road took a back seat during her daughters illness. So her husband and son wrote to Car SOS to help get the car running once more and hopefully help to give Josephine back some of her love of life and return her independence. However, having been left standing in a garage for five years the car had developed chronic rust problems, and its not until the boys get the car back to the Car SOS workshop that they realise just what they have taken on. Virtually every single part of the car is beyond repair. Will the team be able to get the bodywork replaced and the engine started within the three weeks time frame?
